  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nERC1155 didn't define enumerable interface, but can be useful to create one for dApp to use.\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\n```solidity\r\ninterface ERC1155 {\r\n    function totalTokenIds() external view returns (uint256);\r\n    function tokenIdByIndex(uint256 _index) external view returns (uint256);\r\n    function tokenIdByIndexOfOwner(address _owner, uint256 _tokenIndex) external view returns (uint256);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI wonder if there were previous discussion of adding such features\r\n\r\nAlso mentioned in https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts-upgradeable/issues/166",
